        <h1>LeetCode 3513: Number of Unique XOR Triplets I (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an array nums containing distinct integers from 1 to n (a permutation-like structure). A
                triplet XOR value is defined as nums[i] XOR nums[j] XOR nums[k] for distinct indices i, j, k. Return the
                number of unique XOR triplet values that can be formed.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3]<br>
                Output: 4<br>
                Explanation: Since size is 3 (&gt;= 3), bits needed to represent 3 is 2, so answer = 2^2 = 4 unique
                possible XOR values in range.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int uniqueXorTriplets(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int size = nums.size();
        // With less than 3 numbers, the answer is simply n.
        if (size &lt; 3) {
            return size;
        }
        int bits = 0;
        int value = size;
        while (value) {
            value &gt;&gt;= 1;
            bits++;
        }
        return 1 &lt;&lt; bits;
    }
};</code></pre>
